Air fryers are actually a godsend, if you take canned diced potatoes, give it a light covering of olive oil, and slap it in there for about 10 minutes you get perfect crunchy potato cubes to add to whatever dish you're making, its become a favorite of mine in omelets.

As for brussel sprouts, take a cast iron skillet and fry a single piece of bacon in it, then add your brussel sprouts with salt, pepper, and paprika, and it is leagues better. Save the bacon for later in salads, a blt, or as a snack. Try it sometime.
